{
  "stem": "26576.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But when we heard that we are free-- and later on, I spoke to many people, what does it mean to be free?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were thousands and thousands kilometers away from a human being.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had no money.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On one hand, many people stayed on because there was-- it wasn't an easy thing to get out of there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father worked it out that it'll be better for us if we move because he didn't think that we can survive another winter.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So what he decided that we will sell whatever we have, clothes and bed linen and that, just to be able to buy some tickets-- it doesn't matter where-- somewhere to south of Russia.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because south means also warm weather, and warm weather is much easier to survive than in cold weather.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Those were-- anyway, this is how he thought.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Later on, not everything turned out 100%, but we tried to-- to get out of there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were able to come to the big city, which was called Sverdlovsk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why we were-- why we're freed?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was this-- this is actual a very important thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was an agreement.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, the-- the Polish government in exile-- there was a Polish government in exile in London, and the Polish government in exile made a pact with the Russians.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was against Germany.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you know at the beginning, it was the Germans and the Russians, but at that stage, the Polish government in exile made a pact of non-aggression.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And since we were Polish citizens, and we have a government in exile, so they freed us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I heard later on that not every Polish citizen was freed, but we were freed.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
